# admin-api — environment variables
#
# This file documents env vars consumed by the admin-api service.
# Copy and rename to .env (gitignored) and fill in deployment-specific values.

# -- Dispatch-check (optional, scope item #18 of v0.10.6.1) -----------------
# When DISPATCH_CHECK_URL is set, /internal/validate calls an external
# authority for bot-capable tokens to ask whether the underlying user may
# dispatch bots. When unset (default for OSS self-hosters), the gate is
# skipped and validation proceeds unchanged.
#
# The OSS code is intentionally generic — it knows NOTHING about Stripe,
# balances, quotas, or tiers; the authority decides. Only fires for tokens
# whose scopes include "bot" or "legacy"; tx-only / browser-only tokens
# skip the call entirely.
#
# Fail-OPEN policy: network errors / timeouts / 5xx responses allow the
# action through. The authority side is expected to log gate-call-misses
# and reconcile asynchronously.
#
# DISPATCH_CHECK_URL=               # e.g. https://gate.vexa.ai/api/internal
# DISPATCH_CHECK_SECRET=            # optional bearer token sent on every call
# DISPATCH_CHECK_TIMEOUT_S=2.0      # per-call timeout (seconds, float)
